\pard\plain \fi360\sl288\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf4 When we get interested in something it sort of spreads through our minds like an infection. Slowly taking over areas of our thought before we find ourselves consumed by it. It starts simple, with a curiosity, a desire to know more. We start out searching to get a sense of the big picture. Ironically we tend to get our sense of the big picture by looking in at the details and gathering the elements into a category that we can \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93make sense\u8221\'94 out of. It\u8217\'92s this zooming in and out and in and then out again that allows us to start building up an accurate representational model of what we are exploring. Bringing the detailed features into their place in the gestalt. It\u8217\'92s only once we have a sufficiently organized model that we can start exploring this more. }
\par\pard\plain \fi720\sl288\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf4 The process of developing this big picture understanding of some domain requires a lot of work. Unless there is an interest that drives the learning  }
